# Django Cloud Management Tool

Welcome! This project can be run either directly from the USB drive or by cloning the GitHub repository. Choose whichever is easier for you.

---

## Option 1: Run from USB Drive

### Setup Steps:

1. Copy the project folder from the USB to your computer.

2. Open a terminal (Command Prompt / PowerShell / Terminal).

3. Navigate to the project folder:
   ```bash
   cd path/to/project_folder
(Optional but recommended) Create and activate a virtual environment:

On Windows:

python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate
On Mac/Linux:

python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
Install required packages:

pip install -r requirements.txt
Set environment variables:

If you have a .env.example file, copy it to .env and fill in your secret values.

Or set environment variables manually as needed.

Apply database migrations:

python manage.py migrate
(Optional) Create a superuser for admin access:


python manage.py createsuperuser
Run the development server:

python manage.py runserver
Open your browser and visit http://127.0.0.1:8000

Option 2: Clone from GitHub
Setup Steps:
Clone the repository:


git clone https://github.com/yourusername/your-repo-name.git
cd your-repo-name
Follow steps 4 to 10 from Option 1 above to set up and run the project.

Notes
Make sure you have Python 3.8+ and pip installed on your machine.

The .env file (for secrets/configuration) is not included for security reasons. Use the .env.example as a template.

To stop the server, press Ctrl + C in the terminal.

If you face any issues, double-check that dependencies are installed and environment variables are set.

Thank you for checking out the project!
Feel free to reach out for any questions.

Good luck!
